</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Arts Council of Northern Ireland (ACNI) plays a pivotal role in fostering and promoting the arts across the region. Established to champion creativity and support artists and organisations, ACNI's efforts contribute significantly to the cultural, social, and economic well-being of Northern Ireland. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune explores the functions, impact, and legislative framework surrounding ACNI, highlighting best practices for compliance with relevant regulations. Understanding these elements is crucial for organisations that navigate the cultural sector effectively. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-46e3" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-22_ pf-text-1">The Arts Council of Northern Ireland was founded in 1962.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">ACNI distributes around £13 million annually from public funds, including the National Lottery.

<strong>
</strong></li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">Over 150 organisations and countless individual artists benefit from ACNI's funding and support each year.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1">The creative industries contribute approximately £1 billion to Northern Ireland's economy annually, and ACNI plays a central role in this success.


</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-31_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Arts Council of Northern Ireland (ACNI) </strong>- A public body responsible for promoting and developing the arts in Northern Ireland. It provides funding, advocacy, and strategic support to artists and cultural organisations.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Creative industries </strong>- Economic sectors that involve creating, producing, and distributing goods and services that are cultural, artistic, or entertainment-related.
<strong>
</strong></li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Compliance</strong> - Adherence to laws, regulations, guidelines, and specifications relevant to the arts sector, ensuring that practices are ethical, legal, and in line with best standards.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Legislative framework</strong> - The Arts Council of Northern Ireland operates under several key legislation and regulations designed to ensure accountability and effective use of public funds. The primary regulatory frameworks include:



</li></ul><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-43_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Arts Council (Northern Ireland) Order 1995</strong> - This order reconstituted the Arts Council and outlined its powers, functions, and governance structure. It mandates ACNI to develop policies, distribute funds, and support artistic endeavours throughout Northern Ireland.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Public Services (Social Value) Act 2012</strong> - This act requires ACNI to consider how the services they commission and procure can improve the social, economic, and environmental well-being of Northern Ireland.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-48_ pf-text-1"><strong>National Lottery Act 1993 </strong>- Governs the distribution of National Lottery funds, which form a significant part of ACNI's funding sources.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-50_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-51_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-52_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for implementation
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-54_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong> Strategic planning </strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-56_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Develop a clear strategic plan that aligns with ACNI's objectives and legislative requirements. This ensures that all activities are purposeful and contribute to overarching cultural goals.

























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-58_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Governance and accountability
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-60_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Implement robust governance structures to oversee compliance with legal and regulatory obligations. Regular audits and reviews help maintain transparency and accountability.


























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Community engagement
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-64_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Foster strong community ties by involving local artists and organisations in decision-making processes. This helps ensure funded projects meet community needs and reflect diverse cultural expressions.



























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-66_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Monitoring and evaluation
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-68_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Monitor and evaluate funded projects regularly to assess their impact and effectiveness. Use findings to inform future funding decisions and improve programme delivery.




























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-70_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Training and development
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-72_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Invest in ongoing training and development for staff and funded organisations. This helps ensure they know and can comply with relevant legislation and best practices.




























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-74_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-75_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-76_ pf-heading-1-h3">The importance of the Arts Council of Northern Ireland
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-78_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The ACNI is instrumental in ensuring that the arts thrive in Northern Ireland. By providing financial support, strategic guidance, and advocacy, ACNI helps artists and organisations to achieve their creative potential. This support is crucial in a region where the arts play a vital role in community cohesion, economic development, and individual well-being.





























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-80_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-81_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-82_ pf-heading-1-h3">Supporting artists and organisations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-84_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">ACNI offers various grants and funding programmes tailored to the needs of different segments of the arts community. ACNI's funding helps sustain a vibrant cultural ecosystem, from individual artists to large cultural institutions. This financial support enables recipients to create, innovate, and present their work to diverse audiences.






























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-86_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-87_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-88_ pf-heading-1-h3">Compliance with legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-90_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Adhering to legislation and regulations is paramount for organisations receiving ACNI support. Compliance ensures public funds' ethical and practical use, promoting trust and integrity within the cultural sector. Key compliance areas include financial management, project reporting, and adherence to funding conditions outlined by ACNI and relevant legislation.































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-92_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-93_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-94_ pf-heading-1-h3">Enhancing social value through the Arts
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-96_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The Public Services (Social Value) Act 2012 underscores the importance of considering the broader impact of cultural projects. ACNI-funded projects often contribute to social inclusion, community development, and mental well-being, demonstrating the transformative power of the arts.
































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-98_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-99_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-100_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-102_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To maximise the benefits of ACNI support and ensure compliance with relevant legislation:

























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-104_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-105_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engage in continuous learning </strong>- Stay informed about legislative changes and best practices in arts management.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-107_ pf-text-1"><strong>Leverage technology</strong> - Use compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ to streamline regulatory adherence and reporting.


<strong>
</strong></li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-109_ pf-text-1"><strong>Foster collaboration</strong> - Work closely with ACNI and other funded organisations to share knowledge and resources.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-111_ pf-text-1"><strong>Prioritise transparency </strong>- Maintain clear and open communication with stakeholders about project goals, outcomes, and financial management.


